117. **Outcome:** The city begins to hear the dead—and Kira becomes a bridge between worlds;  
118. **Clever Twist:** The flute doesn’t play for the dead. It plays for the *living who remember them*;  
119. **Worldbuilding Feature:** The city’s streets are paved with the echoes of every word ever spoken;  
120. **Scene:** Kira plays—*and the wind carries a name: “Mama.”*  

